title: $:/plugins/rimir/dashboard/readme

! Dashboard

Turn any tiddler into a //dashboard//: a free-form canvas onto which you drop other tiddlers as freely-arrangeable tiles.

!! What it does

* Tag a tiddler with <<tag "$:/tags/rimir/dashboard">> and its body becomes a canvas.
* ''Add tiles'' by dragging tiddlers onto the canvas from anywhere in the wiki, or by typing a title and pressing //Add tile//.
* ''Batch-add by filter'' — type a filter in the box above the canvas and press //Add matching// to drop a tile for every tiddler it selects, arranged in a grid.
* ''Clean'' — remove tiles in one go (with a confirmation). Leave the clean filter empty to clear the whole dashboard, or give a filter to remove only the tiles whose target it selects.
* ''Fit to screen'' — a toolbar toggle that scales the whole board down so everything is visible at once, sized to fit your window — handy on a small display. Shrink-only (a board that already fits is left at full size); the setting is remembered per dashboard, and dragging/resizing stays accurate while fitted.
* ''Fullscreen'' — a toolbar button that shows the dashboard fullscreen (the whole screen, without the wiki chrome); press again or Esc to exit. Combine it with //Fit to screen// to see the entire board at once on a small display.
* ''Move'' a tile by dragging its title bar, ''resize'' it from the bottom-right corner — geometry is saved on release.
* ''Bring-to-front'' — interacting with a tile raises it above the others, and the stacking order persists.
* ''Two tile styles'' — a //window// tile with a title bar, or a //bare// tile that is just the resizable content. Toggle with the ⊟ action. In both styles the controls appear only while you hover the tile and float over the title, so the caption keeps the full width.
* ''Corner controls'' — a tile's controls appear in the corner on hover or keyboard focus. When the target has an external link an ↗ open-external button sits beside the ⋮ //actions// menu, which opens on hover/focus with ⧉ show-in-popup, ⊟ toggle window/bare, × remove (groups offer ＋ add-nested-group and ×).
* ''Collapse a tile'' — window tiles have a ▸/▾ toggle: a collapsed tile shrinks to just its headline, or — if its target has an `icon` — to just that icon (click to expand, drag to move, hover for the caption).
* ''Drop onto a collapsed tile'' — a collapsed tile or group is still a drop target: drop a tiddler or file onto a collapsed //group// to add it as a child (the group then expands), or drop a file onto a collapsed //content tile// whose target is under `work/` to file it alongside that item. No extra chrome — the box is just outlined while you drag over it.
* ''Choose what a tile shows'' — a tile transcludes its target's body by default; an uploaded image or PDF (with a `_thumbnail_uri`) shows its ''thumbnail'', and a tiddler with no text but an `icon` shows the icon. Override per tile from the ⋮ menu (//Show//: auto / body / icon, or any field name), or set per-dashboard ''display rules'' (a target filter → the field to show) from the //Display rules// panel.
* ''Group (meta) tiles'' — press //Add group// for a container tile that is itself a mini-canvas: drop tiddlers into it, drag existing tiles in and out of it, and nest groups inside groups recursively. Whatever you type in the add box becomes the new group's name (you can also rename it inline later). Collapse a group with ▸/▾ and it shrinks to just its header bar (as narrow as its content); expanding restores its previous size and raises it to the front so its contents stay visible. Rename it inline and see its child count. Give a group an `icon` and it shows small before the name — or, when the group is collapsed, becomes the whole header (hover for the name, click to expand). Removing a group promotes its contents to the parent container.
* ''Link a group to a tiddler (its context)'' — a group can be //connected// to a tiddler as its //implicit context//: open the group's ⋮ menu → //Context…// and name a tiddler (or drop a tiddler onto the group's header). The group then adopts that tiddler's caption (editable independently afterwards), shows its [[rimir/kind|$:/plugins/rimir/kind]] icon in the header (click it to open the tiddler in the story river), and — when the context is a kind instance — gains the same ✎ //entity// popup a content tile has, so //Add child// creates instances with `parent` pre-set to the context //and drops their tiles inside this group//. //Unlink// from the same menu (the caption is kept).
* ''Click to open'' — a click (as opposed to a drag) opens the tile's target tiddler in the story river.
* ''Open a link in a new browser tab'' — if a tile's target carries a `url` (or `_canonical_uri`) field, its ''caption is rendered as a link'' (hover to see the address in the browser status bar; click to open it in a new tab). The tile also shows an ↗ action, and ''Ctrl/Cmd-clicking'' the tile does the same — an uploaded image or file tile opens its raw file this way. Plain click elsewhere on the tile still opens the target in the wiki. The fields consulted and their priority are configurable (see the //Settings// tab).
* ''Open a tiddler in a new browser tab'' — for a tile whose target has //no// external link, the ⋮ menu offers an ↗ item that opens the target tiddler itself in a new tab, via its permalink.
* ''Ctrl-drag to duplicate'' — hold Ctrl (or Cmd) as you start dragging a tile to drop a //copy// of it elsewhere (even into another group), leaving the original in place. The same tiddler can appear on as many tiles as you like.
* ''Show contents in a popup'' — the ⧉ control opens the target in a centered popup rendered through TiddlyWiki's default ViewTemplate (title, tags, fields and body), without leaving the dashboard. Close it with the × button or by clicking the backdrop.
* ''Kind-aware'' — when a tile's target is a [[rimir/kind|$:/plugins/rimir/kind]] instance, the window tile shows the type's icon (with the type name as hover text) before the caption. Degrades silently when kind is not installed.
* ''Edit & extend kind entities'' — for a tile whose target is a [[rimir/kind|$:/plugins/rimir/kind]] instance, a ✎ //entity// control appears next to the ⋮ menu; hovering it opens a compact popup (the same actions as //Kind: Instances Overview//): ''edit'' opens the live editor modal, and ''Add child'' offers one button per kind whose `parent` accepts this entity's type — creating the child with `parent` pre-set (same validation and title-formula as the Creator) //and dropping a tile for it into the same group as the source tile//, so it appears right on the dashboard. Only appears when kind is installed and the target is an instance.

!! Quick start

# Click //New dashboard// in the page controls (right sidebar → Tools), or tag any tiddler <<tag "$:/tags/rimir/dashboard">>.
# Drag a few tiddlers onto the canvas.
# Move, resize, and restyle them; click one to open it.

!! How it is stored

Each tile is its own tiddler tagged <<tag "$:/tags/rimir/dashboard/tile">>, stored under `$:/config/rimir/dashboard/<dashboard-id>/tiles/…` with plain fields (`target` / `x` / `y` / `w` / `h` / `z` / `style`). No JSON blobs — every move, resize or restyle is an ordinary `$action-setfield`.

!! Prerequisites

TiddlyWiki >= 5.4.0. No hard dependencies. Optional: [[rimir/kind|$:/plugins/rimir/kind]] (type icons on tiles) and [[rimir/doc-template|$:/plugins/rimir/doc-template]] (branded documentation).
